lead_paragraph: The Penn State women’s team, the top-seeded defending champion, is 36-0 and has not lost a set all season, but it needs two more victories for the national title, starting with Thursday night’s semifinal against No. 4 Nebraska (31-2). The other semifinal in Omaha matches No. 2 Stanford (30-3), the 2007 national runner-up, against No. 3 Texas (29-3). The Lions have won 109 consecutive sets, breaking the 105-set streak set by Florida in 2003. Penn State has also won 62 consecutive matches, another N.C.A.A. record.
